</subtitle><author><name>Ajay Ramesh</name><email>ajaycs14@gmail.com</email></author><entry><title type="html">How to safely share Secrets in Git hub repos.</title><link href="https://notesbyair.github.io//blog/notesbyair.github.io/2019-01-14-donot-share-apikeys-in-git/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How to safely share Secrets in Git hub repos." /><published>2019-01-14T00:00:00-06:00</published><updated>2019-01-14T00:00:00-06:00</updated><id>https://notesbyair.github.io//blog/notesbyair.github.io/donot-share-apikeys-in-git</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://notesbyair.github.io//blog/notesbyair.github.io/2019-01-14-donot-share-apikeys-in-git/">&lt;ul id=&quot;markdown-toc&quot;&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#problem&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-problem&quot;&gt;Problem&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#workshop&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-workshop&quot;&gt;Workshop&lt;/a&gt;    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#one-time-steps&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-one-time-steps&quot;&gt;One-time steps:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#on-every-repository&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-on-every-repository&quot;&gt;On-Every repository:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#adding-trusted-contributor-use-the-existing-secret-key&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-adding-trusted-contributor-use-the-existing-secret-key&quot;&gt;Adding trusted contributor use the existing secret key&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;ul&gt;
          &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#say-your-friend-alice-to-required-to-know-all-the-api-key&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-say-your-friend-alice-to-required-to-know-all-the-api-key&quot;&gt;Say your friend Alice to required to know all the api key.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
          &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#steps-from-alice-side&quot; id=&quot;markdown-toc-steps-from-alice-side&quot;&gt;Steps from Alice side&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;/ul&gt;
      &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h1 id=&quot;problem&quot;&gt;Problem&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qucik solution to the problem -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;Developers keep leaving secret keys to corporate data out in the open for anyone to take&quot;&gt;https://qz.com/674520/companies-are-sharing-their-secret-access-codes-on-github-and-they-may-not-even-know-it/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;Slack bot token leakage exposing business critical information&quot;&gt;https://labs.detectify.com/2016/04/28/slack-bot-token-leakage-exposing-business-critical-information/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h1 id=&quot;workshop&quot;&gt;Workshop&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let’s consider a scenario to work with, say we have API keys to newsapi.org, and your Mobile app uses those keys to fetch the data from NewsAPI org. Now you have finished it, code is committed to Github repo with a secret key.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some other developers want to extend your app to develop the iOS app. All those are your friends, and you decided to remove the secret key and commit it. That is the right decision, but all your friends again need to get the newspaper registration process to get the API key. That process is a productivity killer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So far I found these three solutions, first use Github private repository(not free), seconds to use Bitbucket - it offers some free private repos.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The third option is to use git secrets to share the encrypted file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;one-time-steps&quot;&gt;One-time steps:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Install git secrets. &lt;a href=&quot;Follow this document&quot;&gt;https://git-secret.io/installation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Create a GPG key using below commands.
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;gpg
gpg &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;--list-keys&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Export the public key to some known location.
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;gpg &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;--armor&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;--export&lt;/span&gt; alice@cyb.org &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; alice-public-key.txt
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;on-every-repository&quot;&gt;On-Every repository:&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Initilize the repo.
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;mkdir &lt;/span&gt;donotshare &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;cd &lt;/span&gt;donotshare
git init
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;newsapi=secret-key&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; app.properties
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Initialize the git secret configurations, it will create a .gitsecret folder in your repo.
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git secret init
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;ls&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;-al&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Add all secret files into a .gitignore file.
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;app.properties&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; .gitignore
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Now tell the person who can know the secret using below command.
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git secret tell alice@cyb.org
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Add the file to encrypt it. It will through an error if that file is not present in &lt;strong&gt;.gitignore&lt;/strong&gt; file
    &lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git secret add app.properties
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Now issue the command to hide. It will encrypt all. Note: You should do this before your commit it.
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git secret hide
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Now its safe to commite and push to github.
    &lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git  add .
git commit -m &quot;app properties encrypted&quot;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Cross check in your github account, it will not have &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;app.properties&lt;/code&gt; file, but it will have encrypted &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;app.properties.secret&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;adding-trusted-contributor-use-the-existing-secret-key&quot;&gt;Adding trusted contributor use the existing secret key&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;say-your-friend-alice-to-required-to-know-all-the-api-key&quot;&gt;Say your friend Alice to required to know all the api key.&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Ask his public key via some secure channel. I share the public key via Gmail with encryption and expiry date on. 
Import the public key using
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;gpg &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;--import&lt;/span&gt; alice-public-key.txt
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;After you recieved his public key, add it to the key ring, so that Alice can decrypt using his private key.
    &lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git secret tell alice@cyb.org
git commit &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;-m&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;adding alice public key&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
git push 
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;h3 id=&quot;steps-from-alice-side&quot;&gt;Steps from Alice side&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;language-sh highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;git secret reveal
&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;ls&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nt&quot;&gt;-al&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Knows mistakes or shortcuts: 
You can share your private key with Alice so that he can see secrets without his public key. This is HIGHLY DISCOURAGED.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alice steps to reveal the secret key :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;git pull&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;git secret reveal
 it might ask his private passpharse.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;done.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</content><author><name>Ajay Ramesh</name><email>ajaycs14@gmail.com</email></author><summary type="html"></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">How to safely share Secrets in Git hub repos.</title><link href="https://notesbyair.github.io//blog/2019-01-14-donot-share-apikeys-in-git/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How to safely share Secrets in Git hub repos." /><published>2019-01-14T00:00:00-06:00</published><updated>2019-01-14T00:00:00-06:00</updated><id>https://notesbyair.github.io//blog/donot-share-apikeys-in-git</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://notesbyair.github.io//blog/2019-01-14-donot-share-apikeys-in-git/">&lt;ul id=&quot;markdown-toc&quot;&gt;
